{
  "text": "1284 AIDS 2011, Vol 25 No 10 Data are reported as mean AE SD, unless otherwise indicated. CRP, C-reactive protein; PAI-1, plasminogen activator inhibitor-1; tPA, tissue plasminogen activator. a Data previously published in [CITATION_1] . 1 The values are for the difference between the changes from baseline in the tesamorelin group and the placebo group. [CITATION_2] The values are for the difference between the percentage change from baseline in the tesamorelin group and the placebo group. [CITATION_3] P values are for the comparison between the changes from baseline in the tesamorelin group and the placebo group. 4 P < 0.05 for the within-group change from baseline to week 26 within the tesamorelin group and the placebo group. Changes in tissue plasminogen activator and plasminogen activator inhibitor-1 after continued tesamorelin or withdrawal (26-52 weeks) In the extension dataset, significant changes in tPA antigen seen over the first 26 weeks were sustained during weeks 26-52 in the group that continued tesamorelin (T-T group, change from baseline at 52 weeks \u00c02.66 AE 2.60 ng/ml, P < 0.001 for within group comparison). Among the participants discontinuing tesamorelin during weeks 26-52 (T-P group), the change from baseline at 52 weeks in tPA antigen was \u00c02.19 AE 2.22 ng/ml (P < 0.001 for within group comparison). No significant changes were seen in PAI-1 antigen during the extension phase. As previously published, adiponectin showed a sustained increase in the T-T group but returned to baseline in the T-P group, and there were no significant changes in CRP during the extension phase [CITATION_4] .",
  "correct_citation": {
